  stimulus_text = 'The text of the passage is structured around a claim followed by a series of reasons to support that claim.  The passage then ends by restating the main point in a broader context. Which choice best describes how the author develops the claim made in the passage''s first sentence? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
